Hi Team,

Field name: Balance sheet table
Screenshot attached.

cc : @Elan Sharony @Aditi

Seeing this error in model-service for the field in question:

```2024-11-15T17:43:56.363607139Z stdout F level=INFO time=2024-11-15 17:43:56,363 msg="SQL query: ['It appears that there are no tables in the database based on the provided schema information. Therefore, it is not possible to generate a SQL query to fetch data from a non-existent table.

However, if you provide the schema for the "Balance Sheet Table" or any other table, I can help you construct the appropriate SQL query. For example, if you provide a CREATE TABLE statement for the "Balance Sheet Table," I can use that information to generate the required SQL query.

Please provide the schema or any additional information about the tables in the database.']"  path="/model-service/py/instabase/ibllm/model/tabular_data_framework/table_query/db_handler.py:246" process="MainProcess" thread="ThreadPoolExecutor-426_0" trace_id=""```
cc @Sayd @Nikolaos Kofinas are you able to help debug?

Could we get a quick fix on this please for the time being please? I am unable to decide which documents are the best for my demo as this error keeps happening randomly on different documents for every run. Demo at 3 pm ET :disappointed:
if it happens randomly then the model is the fault probably, I am not an expert on the table models but this is what I afraid is happening
did you use the advance model?
It is using the advanced model. basic model does not give me good results
Sounds like a similar issue I had from this thread (https://instabase.slack.com/archives/C05BJCNKZAM/p1729697062125439). There doesn't seem to be a quick fix at the moment though
Okay I just need to get lucky with one run that has no errors then :lolcry: Will keep trying
Renre customer has the same issue when trying to self serve and have flagged this to @Orlando. There is probably an existing ticket.
